The paper deals with the problem of rendezvous of mobile agents in an unknown environment, which is a common topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of labels to determine the route of each agent suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) perspective. The presence of an adversary that can affect the movement of the agents is related to the study of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the algorithms presented involve geometric concepts and the analysis of paths in graphs, which are typical of computational geometry (cs.CG).
